main event: A civilian graduate student observed a circular object at Lower Souris Wildlife Refuge on July 11, 1966.
interesting points: The object climbed slowly and had blinking lights.,The observation lasted between 1 to 1.5 minutes.,The object was described as circular in shape and consistent with an aircraft.,The witness was a graduate student from the University of North Dakota., The observation was made visually from the ground.
sighted object: a circular-type object with blinking lights
location: Lower Souris Wildlife Refuge, North Dakota, USA
witness description: a graduate student at the University of North Dakota
